---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Explain — Andrew Shiau"
  description="A skill that turns something I figured out into an interactive explainer — a diagram and a quiz."
>
  <div class="grid">
    <div class="back"><a href="/">← Index</a></div>
  </div>

  <div class="grid">
    <div class="c1-10"><div class="shrule"></div><h1>Explain</h1></div>
  </div>
  <div class="grid">
    <p class="dek c1-8" style="margin-top:var(--unit)">
      A skill that turns something I just figured out — an incident, a system, a
      recipe — into a self-contained explainer: a diagram, and a short quiz that
      checks the idea landed.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="grid">
    <div class="c1-8" style="margin-top:calc(var(--unit)*1.5)">
      <p>
        The quiz is the point. Writing something down proves you can phrase it; a
        reader answering three questions right proves it landed in someone else's head.
        The skill builds both from one prompt, in one HTML file, in whichever house
        style fits.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="grid">
    <div class="block c1-6">
      <span class="st">Both examples below are live.</span>
      <span class="sd">Answer a quiz question — correct turns red, wrong gets an ✕.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="grid">
    <div class="rule"></div>
  </div>
  <div class="grid">
    <div class="c1-2"></div>
    <div class="c3-12"><h2>Explainers</h2></div>
  </div>
  <div class="grid" style="margin-top:var(--unit)">
    <div class="links">
      <a href="/writing/10x-is-a-loop/">
        10x is a loop, not a prompt <span class="arrowc">→</span>
        <span class="lu">AI-assisted engineering, from the public research</span>
      </a>
      <a href="/writing/canele/">
        What makes a canelé custardy <span class="arrowc">→</span>
        <span class="lu">one ratio, from six recipes normalized</span>
      </a>
      <a href="/writing/loops-vs-graphs/">
        Loops vs graphs <span class="arrowc">→</span>
        <span class="lu">agent architecture — when a loop should become a graph</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="grid">
    <div class="rule"></div>
  </div>
  <div class="grid">
    <div class="facts">
      <div class="frow">
        <div class="fm">Form</div>
        <div class="ftx">
          One prompt in, one self-contained HTML file out — explanation, a diagram,
          and a scored quiz. Set in whichever house style suits the piece.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="frow">
        <div class="fm">Why the quiz</div>
        <div class="ftx">
          Anyone can write a thing down. A reader passing the quiz is the proof it
          worked. That's the bar.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
